	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Mon Jan 30, 2012 3:47 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I found a bug. Look at this disassembly:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">ZS8031:<br />&nbsp; ; X is 0 at this point<br />&nbsp; lda #$20<br />&nbsp; sta PPUADDR<br />&nbsp; lda #$00<br />&nbsp; sta PPUADDR<br />ZS803B:<br />&nbsp; ldy #$40<br />ZS803D:<br />&nbsp; sta PPUDATA<br />&nbsp; iny<br />&nbsp; bne ZS803D<br />&nbsp; inx<br />&nbsp; bne ZS803B</div>
<br />This looks like it was supposed to just clear the nametables. But it ends up clearing 49,152 bytes (192 in each inner loop, times 256 repetitions of the outer loop). This passes over the PPU's entire address space three times, including the pattern table areas. On a board with CHR RAM, this ends up clearing everything out of the pattern tables.
<br />
<br />Changing the LDY #$40 to LDY #$F0 allows the game to work. I've added the following patch to the game's information in Action 53:
<br />patches=803C:F0

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


